            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "\nI am a parent of a 5-year-old child who was studying in JKG-A at Nirmala Convent School, Kharadi. I am deeply disappointed and disheartened by the treatment we have received from the school administration.\n\nMy son was forced to give a re-exam three times for UKG admission, and even after that, the principal insisted on another re-exam. These tests were taken in a large, empty classroom, while we parents were made to sit far away from the school premises. My child was scared and anxious, and it was emotionally distressing to see a 5-year-old being put under such pressure. As per government rules, promotion till Class 8 is automatic. So why is the school repeatedly subjecting a small child to re-examinations?\n\nThis entire situation started when we requested the class teacher, Ms. Jessy, to let our son participate in the annual day since he sings and dances very well. Our request was ignored, and we never received an invitation to the event – unlike other parents. When we questioned this and a few other academic concerns, the treatment from the school completely changed. We now feel we are being deliberately harassed and misled about our son's admission.\n\nWe also raised our concerns via email in April, but we received no response from the school. For over two months, we were given false promises regarding admission dates. It is now June, and most schools have closed their admissions. Due to this delay, our son's entire academic year is at risk – a loss that cannot be recovered.\n\nThis review is written in the hope that no other child or parent has to go through such mental stress and emotional trauma. I sincerely request the education authorities to look into this matter seriously.\n\n",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
